======================================================================

The NCAR Command Language (NCL) is a software project developed by the
Computational & Information Systems Laboratory at the National Center
for Atmospheric Research (NCAR), and funded by the National Science
Foundation.

NCL is an interpreted language that is tailored for the scientific
analysis and visualization of climate and weather data.

======================================================================
Documentation
======================================================================

NCL has extensive documentation available at:

    http://www.ncl.ucar.edu/

======================================================================
Installing NCL
======================================================================

We recommend you install NCL via conda:

http://www.ncl.ucar.edu/Download/conda.shtml

======================================================================
Reporting bugs
======================================================================

If you'd like to report a bug, please use the NCL GitHub repo:

   http://github.com/ncar/ncl

======================================================================
Help with NCL
======================================================================

If you have any problems installing or using NCL, post them
on one of our two email lists. You must subscribe first:

Installation questions and help: 

   ncl-install@ucar.edu

Subscribe via:

   http://mailman.ucar.edu/mailman/listinfo/ncl-install

Usage questions/help:

   ncl-talk@ucar.edu

Subscribe via:

   http://mailman.ucar.edu/mailman/listinfo/ncl-talk

----------------------------------------------------------------------

Detailed instructions for building NCL from source code or installing
from pre-built binaries can be found at:

  http://www.ncl.ucar.edu/Download/

----------------------------------------------------------------------
